WEBVTT

00:00.601 --> 00:04.970
♪♪♪

00:04.972 --> 00:06.704
(footsteps shuffle)

00:08.442 --> 00:14.313
♪♪♪

00:14.448 --> 00:17.349
Neil: Here! Now!

00:17.484 --> 00:19.717
Live!

00:19.719 --> 00:21.886
(screaming) ahhhhhhhhhhhhhhhh!

00:24.191 --> 00:26.057
We bottle up our emotions,

00:26.093 --> 00:28.526
We're afraid of being
our full selves.

00:29.963 --> 00:32.464
Don't regret the past.

00:32.599 --> 00:34.532
Don't fear the future.

00:35.870 --> 00:38.203
Let it out.

00:38.205 --> 00:39.805
Be free!

00:41.542 --> 00:42.874
Ahhhhhhhhhhhhhh!

00:42.910 --> 00:45.277
All: (screaming) ahhhhhhhhhhh!

00:45.346 --> 00:48.346
(jenny is silent as everyone
else screams)

00:48.382 --> 00:50.015
<i> Neil: (yells) let it go!</i>

00:50.150 --> 00:52.584
All: (screaming) ahhhhhhhhhhh!
Neil: (yells) let it go!

00:53.621 --> 00:57.823
♪♪♪

00:57.892 --> 00:59.424
<i>Female reporter: In other news,</i>

00:59.426 --> 01:01.293
<i> Provincial medical officials</i>
<i> are investigating a case</i>

01:01.428 --> 01:04.529
<i> They say may be linked</i>
<i> to the new corona virus.</i>

01:04.598 --> 01:07.900
(footsteps thud)

01:07.902 --> 01:10.502
♪♪♪

01:10.504 --> 01:12.504
(doors slide open)

01:12.639 --> 01:16.441
♪♪♪

01:16.477 --> 01:18.776
(doors slide open)

01:18.813 --> 01:20.712
(distorted music)

01:20.781 --> 01:23.982
♪♪♪

01:23.984 --> 01:25.517
(gurney rattles)

01:25.519 --> 01:29.588
♪♪♪

01:29.590 --> 01:32.191
(ominous, distorted music)

01:32.193 --> 01:33.925
(doors slide open)

01:33.961 --> 01:37.595
♪♪♪

01:37.631 --> 01:38.997
(doors slide open)

01:41.402 --> 01:43.268
<i> Female reporter: Our framework</i>
<i> to minimize the risks</i>

01:43.270 --> 01:45.737
<i> In canada seems</i>
<i> to be responsive</i>

01:45.739 --> 01:48.340
<i> According to the world</i>
<i> health organization,</i>

01:48.409 --> 01:51.610
<i>Who is calling it sophisticated</i>
<i> and extremely efficient...</i>

01:51.679 --> 01:53.745
♪♪♪

01:53.747 --> 01:55.480
(doors slide open)

01:57.451 --> 01:58.817
(bag rustles)

02:00.087 --> 02:01.820
Male reporter: Families across
canada

02:01.822 --> 02:03.422
<i> Are barred from seeing</i>
<i> their loved ones</i>

02:03.557 --> 02:05.490
<i> As long-term care homes</i>
<i> lockdown</i>

02:05.559 --> 02:07.759
<i> Due to rising covid cases.</i>

02:07.895 --> 02:10.428
<i> They're often left with</i>
<i> no accesses or information.</i>

02:10.498 --> 02:17.502
♪♪♪

02:17.505 --> 02:25.510
♪♪♪

02:25.546 --> 02:27.512
(cupboard door creaks open)

02:27.515 --> 02:28.780
(boxes rustle)

02:28.916 --> 02:30.382
What's this?

02:30.384 --> 02:31.850
(boxes rustle)

02:31.919 --> 02:33.117
(frustrated) oh...

02:33.154 --> 02:34.453
(cupboard door bangs shut)
mitch!

02:34.455 --> 02:37.055
♪♪♪

02:37.124 --> 02:39.524
There are no more masks!

02:39.593 --> 02:41.759
We can't keep doing this!

02:42.796 --> 02:45.464
♪♪♪

02:45.466 --> 02:48.400
- Oh hey, mike.
Need a mask?

02:48.469 --> 02:50.002
I made these.

02:50.004 --> 02:52.204
- Thanks, bobby,
you're amazing.

02:52.273 --> 02:54.206
(door creaks open)

02:54.341 --> 02:56.408
(gurneys rattle)

02:56.477 --> 02:58.810
♪♪♪

03:00.347 --> 03:02.380
(gurneys rattle loudly)

03:03.884 --> 03:06.017
(music builds)

03:07.288 --> 03:14.293
♪♪♪

03:14.295 --> 03:16.895
(door bursts open)

03:16.964 --> 03:19.298
(gurneys rattle)

03:19.433 --> 03:21.967
(operatic music plays)

03:21.969 --> 03:28.907
♪♪♪

03:28.976 --> 03:32.978
♪♪♪

03:32.980 --> 03:35.314
(music becomes distorted)

03:35.316 --> 03:40.518
♪♪♪

03:40.588 --> 03:43.121
♪♪♪

03:43.190 --> 03:45.724
(operatic music plays)

03:45.793 --> 03:48.192
(siren wails)

03:48.229 --> 03:51.663
♪♪♪

03:51.798 --> 03:54.266
(police radio chatter echoes)

03:54.401 --> 03:57.869
(operatic music plays)

03:59.073 --> 04:00.272
(door clicks open)

04:00.407 --> 04:01.940
(sharp exhale)

04:02.009 --> 04:04.943
♪♪♪

04:05.012 --> 04:06.611
(plastic bag rustles)

04:06.614 --> 04:09.748
♪♪♪

04:09.750 --> 04:11.582
(whispers a prayer)

04:12.620 --> 04:14.686
(operatic music plays)

04:14.722 --> 04:19.657
♪♪♪

04:20.894 --> 04:22.494
(operatic music echoes
and fades)

04:26.433 --> 04:28.700
(cars honk,
police radio chatter)

04:28.769 --> 04:30.502
(jackhammer rattles
in the distance)

04:30.571 --> 04:32.271
Donovan: Ah! Stupid face
shield! (shield thumps)

04:34.575 --> 04:36.308
Jenny: The airbag
didn't deploy.

04:36.443 --> 04:37.609
Donovan: Ah, it was probably
in an accident,

04:37.744 --> 04:39.344
Someone sold it to her cheap.

04:40.514 --> 04:41.947
Her head hit the steering wheel?

04:42.082 --> 04:44.315
<i> - Yeah, she wasn't wearing her</i>
<i> seatbelt.</i>

04:44.351 --> 04:46.651
There's blood around her nose.

04:46.687 --> 04:48.387
(door squeaks opens)

04:48.389 --> 04:50.255
(traffic rumbles nearby)

04:50.257 --> 04:52.724
The steering wheel
is bedazzled.

04:52.726 --> 04:54.993
There is bruising on her arm.

04:54.995 --> 04:56.395
(items rustle in the glove box)

04:56.530 --> 04:58.897
(police radio chatter and
jack hammering in the distance)

04:59.032 --> 05:01.132
- Her name's "roberta almeda."

05:01.168 --> 05:02.401
At least we have an address.

05:04.738 --> 05:06.538
Pop the trunk for me.
(glove box clicks shut)

05:06.540 --> 05:08.006
<i> (trunk pops open)</i>

05:08.075 --> 05:10.808
(donovan's phone rings)

05:10.844 --> 05:12.344
- Yeah.

05:12.479 --> 05:15.547
(traffic rumbles nearby)

05:15.549 --> 05:18.616
♪♪♪

05:18.652 --> 05:20.385
- I know you.

05:22.890 --> 05:25.357
- All right. Yeah, yeah.

05:27.161 --> 05:28.459
<i> All right, let me know.</i>

05:31.098 --> 05:32.630
- What's that?
- Brownie mix.

05:32.700 --> 05:34.399
She's got a trunk full of it.

05:37.704 --> 05:39.704
- What are you looking for?

05:39.707 --> 05:41.139
(rustling)

05:41.274 --> 05:44.442
- Receipt. She paid for all
this at 8:53 last night.

05:46.447 --> 05:49.514
- So she's shopping so she
can covid-bake and then...

05:50.918 --> 05:52.384
What? Somebody attacks her
and she tries to get away,

05:52.453 --> 05:54.386
And slams into a pole?

05:54.521 --> 05:56.855
- Well, it could be carjacking.

05:56.924 --> 05:58.890
We didn't, we didn't find
a purse.

05:58.892 --> 06:00.958
- She had a... A debit card
in her pocket.

06:00.994 --> 06:02.961
- Never a carjacking
when you want it to be.

06:03.096 --> 06:04.862
- She was a frontline worker.

06:04.898 --> 06:08.299
She's got bruises on her nose
and cheekbones.

06:09.870 --> 06:12.671
- All right. Let me know
what the autopsy says.

06:14.575 --> 06:17.142
♪♪♪

06:17.277 --> 06:19.378
- Hey! Is your leg still
bugging you?

06:19.513 --> 06:21.380
- No.

06:24.118 --> 06:26.217
(water runs and splashes
in the basin)

06:28.689 --> 06:34.292
♪♪♪

06:34.294 --> 06:36.561
(paper towel tears)

06:36.597 --> 06:43.502
♪♪♪

06:43.637 --> 06:46.505
♪♪♪

06:46.640 --> 06:48.773
(bandaid wrapper crinkles)

06:48.842 --> 06:50.976
(someone hums and sings
puccini's "o mio babbino caro")

06:50.978 --> 06:53.178
♪ o mio babbino caro ♪

06:54.648 --> 06:59.016
♪ mi piace è bello, bello ♪

07:00.788 --> 07:02.620
- Hey.
- Hey.

07:03.924 --> 07:06.157
She was a healthcare worker.
One of us.

07:07.194 --> 07:08.793
- Does she look familiar
to you?

07:08.796 --> 07:10.295
I mean, I feel like
I've seen her before,

07:10.430 --> 07:12.363
I just, I can't,
I can't place her.

07:12.433 --> 07:13.665
- No.

07:13.800 --> 07:16.201
- The mechanism of death
is exsanguination.

07:16.203 --> 07:18.236
- She bled out?

07:18.371 --> 07:20.405
- From her nose.
Her skull is cracked.

07:20.540 --> 07:22.840
This is a terrible death
for a young woman.

07:24.344 --> 07:26.244
- She's got a bandaid
on her forehead.

07:26.280 --> 07:28.446
She has bruising on her arms.

07:28.449 --> 07:30.281
- There's a small deep cut.
(tearing sound)

07:30.317 --> 07:31.683
- I mean,
maybe it's domestic abuse.

07:31.818 --> 07:33.751
He followed her to the parking
lot and attacked her there?

07:33.787 --> 07:36.521
- Hmm...
- What?

07:37.691 --> 07:40.225
- I'm not the most experienced
bedazzler,

07:40.227 --> 07:43.160
But this looks like
a real jewel.

07:43.197 --> 07:45.396
- Oh... Well...

07:47.434 --> 07:48.700
(gem rattles)

07:48.769 --> 07:50.435
- How did that get in there?

07:50.437 --> 07:52.303
- I don't know,

07:52.339 --> 07:55.439
But I think our girl
was a rare gem.

07:57.711 --> 08:02.046
♪♪♪

08:02.115 --> 08:04.282
- (grunts in pain)

08:04.318 --> 08:06.784
- Uh, yeah, I need to make
an appointment about my foot.

08:06.820 --> 08:09.387
I busted it last year.

08:09.389 --> 08:11.723
<i> Mcavoy, yeah.</i>

08:11.792 --> 08:13.792
Donovan.

08:13.794 --> 08:15.527
That's great.
All right, thanks.

08:16.663 --> 08:18.163
Malik: Think fast!

08:18.298 --> 08:19.965
Found these in bobby almeda's
apartment,

08:20.100 --> 08:22.601
Along with a hamster wearing
a homemade sweater.

08:22.736 --> 08:24.201
She was a psw.

08:24.238 --> 08:26.137
Worked in six different
nursing homes in the gta.

08:26.273 --> 08:27.706
- That's a no-no.

08:27.708 --> 08:29.941
- Yeah, you can't be spreading
your germs all over old people.

08:29.943 --> 08:31.443
- Which one was she working
at last?

08:31.578 --> 08:33.244
- Uh, linden tree
long-term care.

08:33.313 --> 08:35.413
(id tags rustle)

08:37.484 --> 08:40.285
(bunny suits rustle)
(muffled pa announcement)

08:40.287 --> 08:42.820
- Did she have a partner?
- No. Single.

08:42.856 --> 08:44.856
Hi there.
I'm detective mcavoy, this--

08:44.991 --> 08:46.958
- Jenny cooper. We've met.

08:47.027 --> 08:49.561
I'm here all the time because
of his 21 elderly patients

08:49.563 --> 08:52.531
Who have died of covid
in the last month.

08:52.666 --> 08:54.699
- I see their faces
when I sleep.

08:54.834 --> 08:56.768
Not that I've really slept
since March.

08:56.770 --> 08:58.436
(bag rustles)

08:58.505 --> 09:00.838
- She work here?
- That's bobby.

09:00.840 --> 09:03.642
- She died.
- I know, I just heard.

09:03.644 --> 09:05.777
Man: Is bobby here?
Psw: No, sweetheart, I'm sorry.

09:05.779 --> 09:07.546
Man: Mr. Davis,
let's go back to your room.

09:07.681 --> 09:09.214
- Hey, can you hold this?
(bag rustles)

09:09.349 --> 09:10.982
- So, you know anyone who
might be angry with her?

09:11.051 --> 09:12.917
Mitch: No, she was very well
liked.

09:12.920 --> 09:14.653
(bunny suit rustles)

09:14.655 --> 09:16.854
(keypad beeps, door buzzes,
clicks open)

09:18.892 --> 09:22.293
♪♪♪

09:24.598 --> 09:26.665
<i> (muffled pa announcement)</i>

09:26.667 --> 09:28.199
(knocking)

09:28.268 --> 09:30.768
- Hi. I'm jenny cooper,
I'm the coroner.

09:30.770 --> 09:32.837
Did you know bobby almeda?

09:34.141 --> 09:35.674
- I just, I can't believe it
about bobby.

09:35.676 --> 09:37.342
- I'm sorry.

09:37.344 --> 09:40.277
Um, can I... Can I help? I'm...

09:41.315 --> 09:42.814
- (sighs heavily) yeah.

09:42.883 --> 09:44.982
That would, that would be
great, thank you.

09:47.153 --> 09:49.286
(sheets rustle)

09:49.323 --> 09:51.389
- Did bobby die of covid?

09:51.524 --> 09:53.958
- No. No, I don't think so.

09:56.563 --> 09:57.829
- She loved the elders.

09:57.898 --> 10:00.098
She would bake them treats
that she would bring in.

10:00.100 --> 10:01.766
She even would sewed us masks

10:01.835 --> 10:03.635
When management wouldn't
give them to us.

10:03.770 --> 10:06.171
- But you have an n95s now,
right?

10:06.306 --> 10:08.239
- My brother works in
construction,

10:08.375 --> 10:10.408
So I spray this thing
with lysol every night.

10:10.477 --> 10:11.976
<i> (muffled pa announcement)</i>

10:14.748 --> 10:16.580
(sighs) yeah.

10:16.617 --> 10:18.116
- That's kind of beautiful.

10:18.118 --> 10:20.284
I mean, it's sad,
but it's... Beautiful.

10:21.355 --> 10:23.053
- Yeah. Not everyone
understands, you know,

10:23.055 --> 10:25.123
That you can't have visits.

10:25.125 --> 10:27.392
Actually,
bobby had a run-in here.

10:27.527 --> 10:28.893
Jenny: With who?

10:28.929 --> 10:30.428
Gloria: I don't know.
Some guy.

10:30.497 --> 10:32.129
Ah, my ring always does this...

10:33.199 --> 10:34.965
(rips and snaps)
sorry.

10:36.336 --> 10:38.202
(muffled) I didn't hear
what was said, and then...

10:38.271 --> 10:41.305
She went up to him
and then all of a sudden...

10:42.376 --> 10:44.208
Bam!

10:44.277 --> 10:45.943
- (relieved exhale)

10:45.979 --> 10:47.812
I know how the gem
got in her forehead.

10:47.848 --> 10:49.681
- Are we talking the bedazzling
on the steering wheel?

10:49.750 --> 10:51.883
- No, uh, jewelry!
There was a...

10:51.952 --> 10:54.018
A small gem in the cut
on her forehead.

10:54.087 --> 10:55.953
- Okay.
- I just found out

10:56.023 --> 10:57.689
That bobby got into a fight

10:57.824 --> 10:59.357
With one of the patient's
relatives.

10:59.426 --> 11:01.426
- A physical fight?
- Yeah! I mean, what if,

11:01.428 --> 11:03.527
What if he followed her to the
parking lot and then just--

11:03.563 --> 11:04.829
Donovan: Did you get a name?

11:04.831 --> 11:06.731
- No. Put your fist up.

11:08.568 --> 11:10.168
(light thuds)
- wha...?

11:11.304 --> 11:13.104
- He was wearing a ring.

11:14.574 --> 11:15.973
- All right, so your theory

11:16.009 --> 11:17.775
Is that someone's mysterious
relative,

11:17.844 --> 11:19.444
Wearing a bejeweled ring...
(car alarm beeps off)

11:19.513 --> 11:21.312
- Followed her to the big box
parking lot.

11:21.381 --> 11:23.748
They got in a confrontation,
and then he attacked her.

11:25.385 --> 11:26.951
- Why?
- Don't know.

11:28.155 --> 11:29.888
Uh, maybe he couldn't see
his parent or grandparent,

11:30.023 --> 11:31.555
And he was upset.

11:31.591 --> 11:32.857
- I'll check their security
footage.

11:32.926 --> 11:34.726
- Did you get anything
from the manager?

11:34.795 --> 11:37.395
- Oh, he blamed her for
working in multiple homes.

11:37.397 --> 11:39.997
Suggested not too subtly that
she had brought the virus here.

11:40.033 --> 11:42.066
- I knew I recognized her.

11:42.135 --> 11:44.902
I mean, I've been here
so many times, donovan.

11:46.005 --> 11:47.939
I just, I never even
registered the psws.

11:47.941 --> 11:49.741
- You're not a saint,

11:49.810 --> 11:52.210
And everyone's wearing a mask.

11:52.279 --> 11:54.012
- Yeah.

11:54.147 --> 11:55.880
(plastic bags rustle)
- hey! Hey!

11:55.949 --> 11:57.414
- Hey.

11:57.451 --> 12:00.218
- We're having a little
memorial for bobby!

12:00.220 --> 12:02.620
I wrote down where.
You should come!

12:03.823 --> 12:06.157
- Yeah.
- Okay.
- Thank you.

12:06.159 --> 12:07.892
(birds chirp)

12:07.894 --> 12:09.394
<i> (donovan slams car trunk)</i>

12:09.396 --> 12:11.830
(clink)
(paper rustles)

12:11.832 --> 12:14.432
(seagulls cry)

12:14.434 --> 12:15.734
(paper crinkles)

12:18.071 --> 12:19.704
(tires crunch on gravel)

12:19.839 --> 12:22.774
(slow jazz music plays)

12:25.645 --> 12:27.912
(engine shuts off,
doors click open)

12:29.282 --> 12:31.783
♪ your kisses have stopped ♪

12:33.253 --> 12:36.720
♪ they'll never be topped ♪

12:36.757 --> 12:40.124
♪ my love lingers on ♪

12:40.193 --> 12:41.926
(mailbox creaks open)

12:43.497 --> 12:46.264
♪ time they say ♪

12:46.333 --> 12:48.966
♪ heals a broken heart ♪

12:50.203 --> 12:54.104
♪ but for me there
just is no cure ♪

12:56.276 --> 12:57.474
(mail rustles)

12:57.511 --> 13:00.144
♪ for deep in my soul ♪

13:00.147 --> 13:02.480
♪ you know, you're my goal ♪

13:04.284 --> 13:07.352
♪ my love lingers on ♪

13:08.555 --> 13:10.154
(envelope crinkles)

13:10.157 --> 13:12.957
♪ since you went away ♪

13:12.993 --> 13:16.160
♪ my heart,
all it can only say ♪

13:17.964 --> 13:21.566
♪ my love still lingers on ♪

13:21.635 --> 13:23.768
(door opens)

13:23.770 --> 13:25.370
(door shuts)

13:27.507 --> 13:29.507
Gordon: Hey, smiler.
- Hey, dad.

13:30.977 --> 13:35.112
- Would you believe I actually
saw a ross's goose today?

13:35.182 --> 13:38.116
Is that a sign or what?
A "ross's goose."

13:38.118 --> 13:39.717
- (chuckles softly)

13:39.786 --> 13:42.387
(loon cries in the distance)
jenny: (pensive exhale)

13:42.522 --> 13:44.655
- Is everything okay?

13:44.724 --> 13:46.190
- I um...

13:47.594 --> 13:49.793
(envelope rustles)

13:49.830 --> 13:52.263
Finally got a letter
from liam.

13:52.265 --> 13:53.898
(dog barks in the distance)

13:55.368 --> 13:58.336
- (sighs) oh kiddo.
- Dad. You gotta keep your...

13:58.405 --> 14:00.471
- No, it's okay.
You're a way over there,

14:00.473 --> 14:01.940
And I'm way the hell over here.

14:02.075 --> 14:04.609
Come on, take off your mask.
Let's see that face.

14:05.879 --> 14:06.878
Please?

14:09.082 --> 14:10.748
<i> There she is.</i>

14:10.817 --> 14:13.217
'kay, what's in the letter?

14:13.286 --> 14:14.952
- You know, it's been five
months of nothing,

14:15.021 --> 14:16.754
And now I get...
- What, are you afraid

14:16.823 --> 14:18.723
Of something?
What're you afraid of?

14:22.495 --> 14:24.428
- I know it's a goodbye.

14:24.497 --> 14:26.631
- Oh. You still love him.

14:29.302 --> 14:30.801
(house groans,
night insects buzz)

14:30.871 --> 14:32.904
So, what do you, what do you,
what do you wanna do?

14:40.881 --> 14:43.915
- (tearing up) I don't know,
I just...

14:43.984 --> 14:46.651
I just, I can't... Like I just,
I can't face this right now.

14:46.653 --> 14:48.953
I just can't. I'm so ti...
I'm so tired.

14:50.724 --> 14:52.790
Can you hold onto it for me?
I just, I feel like

14:52.792 --> 14:54.659
I'll put it somewhere
and I'll just lose it.

14:54.728 --> 14:56.527
- Sure. I can do that.
- Thank you.

14:56.663 --> 14:59.396
- I'll just remind you though
I have dementia.

14:59.432 --> 15:02.399
- (laughs) yeah.

