31:04.964 --> 31:07.163
- Oh yeah.
(gasps)

31:07.199 --> 31:09.165
(bird chirps)

31:09.235 --> 31:10.800
- Shh...

31:11.971 --> 31:14.170
- (whispering) wow...

31:14.206 --> 31:17.307
(high-pitched cry,
echoing wing beats)

31:18.444 --> 31:20.243
(sighs) oh...
- Oh no.

31:20.246 --> 31:22.712
- Okay, well, at least
we can tell mom we saw one.

31:22.748 --> 31:24.380
(birds chirp, crows caw,
branch rustles)

31:24.516 --> 31:31.388
♪♪♪

31:31.390 --> 31:32.990
<i> Male reporter: Premier</i>
<i> doug ford spoke out today</i>

31:33.125 --> 31:36.059
<i>About the treatment of patients</i>
<i> in long-term care facilities,</i>

31:36.194 --> 31:37.760
<i> Calling for full transparency</i>

31:37.796 --> 31:39.997
<i> And even suggesting</i>
<i> criminal charges.</i>

31:39.999 --> 31:42.398
<i> Which begs the question,</i>
<i> will he follow through?</i>

31:42.434 --> 31:44.834
(box thumps loudly)

31:44.870 --> 31:46.904
- Okay...

31:47.039 --> 31:48.872
(files thud heavily,
box rattles)

31:48.874 --> 31:50.941
- My focus for the inquest

31:51.010 --> 31:54.611
Will be on infection control.
- You mean use of ppe?

31:54.680 --> 31:57.213
- Yeah, that's, uh, one facet.

31:57.283 --> 31:59.215
Linden tree didn't give
their workers masks,

31:59.217 --> 32:01.385
Even though they knew covid
was in the facility.

32:01.520 --> 32:02.953
- As the crown attorney

32:03.022 --> 32:04.955
Speaking for the coroner's
office, I'm on your side,

32:05.090 --> 32:06.690
But can you prove that?

32:06.825 --> 32:08.891
- Yeah. I sequestered
their garbage back in April.

32:09.028 --> 32:11.228
<i>No n95s, and no surgical masks.</i>

32:11.363 --> 32:13.964
- Very nice.
- Thanks.

32:14.099 --> 32:17.567
- Found a whistleblower-type
complaint in their email.

32:17.636 --> 32:19.769
That's my sequestered garbage.

32:24.510 --> 32:25.709
(inhales sharply)

32:25.711 --> 32:27.644
- Okay. Uh...

32:27.713 --> 32:28.979
(reading) "I've been
working for three years.

32:29.114 --> 32:31.248
You don't care about the staff
or the elderly residents.

32:31.383 --> 32:33.383
People are dying every day
of covid.

32:33.385 --> 32:34.718
You say it's pneumonia.

32:34.720 --> 32:37.854
You say wearing masks will
scare the residents.

32:37.923 --> 32:40.524
You're killing people.
We need protection!

32:43.062 --> 32:45.729
Bobby almeda."

32:45.864 --> 32:52.268
♪♪♪

32:52.304 --> 32:55.072
- What?
(footsteps echo)

32:55.074 --> 32:56.740
- Um...

32:56.742 --> 32:58.075
(whoosh, echoing footsteps
return to normal)

32:58.077 --> 32:59.743
(low hum of chatter,
phones ring)

32:59.745 --> 33:01.478
Uh, nothing.
Uh... She died.

33:01.480 --> 33:04.147
We just, uh,
we never figured it out.

33:04.183 --> 33:06.616
<i> - Huh.</i>

33:06.652 --> 33:08.151
- Did anybody get back to her?

33:08.153 --> 33:10.220
(paper flutters)

33:12.424 --> 33:14.624
- It says that she
was disciplined

33:14.626 --> 33:16.626
For giving the residents...

33:18.230 --> 33:20.497
Uh, the residents weed
brownies.

33:20.499 --> 33:22.265
- They didn't fire her.
- Uh, no.

33:22.400 --> 33:24.835
They, uh... She must've
threatened to go public.

33:24.837 --> 33:26.036
<i> Clark: Linden tree's</i>
<i> parent company,</i>

33:26.171 --> 33:27.837
Care orchard, sent some video.

33:27.873 --> 33:29.573
Linden tree said they
implemented strict protocols

33:29.708 --> 33:31.241
As soon as the outbreak
started.

33:31.243 --> 33:32.576
<i> Staggered start times</i>
<i> for staff,</i>

33:32.711 --> 33:35.078
<i> Hand sanitizer</i>
<i> at all workstations...</i>

33:35.214 --> 33:36.246
<i> And entrances.</i>

33:36.381 --> 33:37.514
<i> Jenny: Mm-kay.</i>

33:37.516 --> 33:39.049
<i> There's gloria.</i>

33:44.757 --> 33:46.656
<i> He's switching the bottle.</i>

33:50.996 --> 33:53.030
<i> That's bobby.</i>

33:53.165 --> 33:55.198
Wait. Um, show me the next day?

33:55.200 --> 33:56.766
- 'kay.

34:01.273 --> 34:03.673
<i> - He's switching</i>
<i> the bottle again.</i>

34:09.915 --> 34:13.316
Why is bobby the only one
who gets the small sanitizer?

34:15.420 --> 34:17.087
I thought it was ingestion
over time.

34:17.222 --> 34:18.855
It's uh... It's absorption.

34:18.891 --> 34:21.424
Um, are there any uh...

34:21.460 --> 34:23.560
Code violations
for linden tree?

34:23.562 --> 34:25.796
- Yeah, yeah. There's a...

34:25.931 --> 34:27.230
There's a bunch.

34:32.637 --> 34:34.704
- What're you looking for?
- (muttering to herself)

34:36.775 --> 34:38.108
Mice.

34:39.211 --> 34:41.244
<i> (phone rings in the distance)</i>

34:42.314 --> 34:43.847
<i> Mitch: You're back.</i>

34:43.916 --> 34:46.316
<i> No new cases today,</i>
<i> happy to report!</i>

34:46.385 --> 34:47.784
- Step away from the counter,
please.

34:47.919 --> 34:49.119
- What's going on?

34:49.254 --> 34:51.354
- I have a warrant to search
these premises.

34:51.423 --> 34:55.659
♪♪♪

34:55.794 --> 34:58.595
(doors slide opened and closed)

34:58.664 --> 35:00.997
(cupboard door bangs shut)

35:05.003 --> 35:06.870
(rustling)

35:09.741 --> 35:11.240
Bingo.

35:16.281 --> 35:18.080
- Swapped it out each time
for her.

35:18.117 --> 35:19.883
Mitch: No.
- No?

35:19.952 --> 35:21.485
Okay, here.

35:21.620 --> 35:24.354
(baggie rustles)
put out your hands. Use it.

35:24.489 --> 35:26.156
Come on.

35:26.291 --> 35:29.091
- I-I just thought she'd
get sick and go away.

35:30.896 --> 35:32.295
(baggie rustles)

35:32.297 --> 35:36.032
- Well, she wasn't that kind
of person.

35:36.034 --> 35:37.634
- Mitch gnatek,
you're under arrest

35:37.636 --> 35:39.435
For the murder of bobby almeda.

35:39.505 --> 35:46.509
♪♪♪

35:46.512 --> 36:03.459
♪♪♪

36:03.529 --> 36:10.533
♪♪♪

36:10.536 --> 36:17.540
♪♪♪

36:17.543 --> 36:24.480
♪♪♪

36:24.550 --> 36:31.554
♪♪♪

36:31.557 --> 36:38.428
♪♪♪

36:38.497 --> 36:43.633
♪♪♪

36:50.542 --> 36:52.508
(blanket rustles)

36:59.151 --> 37:00.917
<i> Dr. Cheng: Lidocaine should be</i>
<i> kicking in.</i>

37:01.987 --> 37:03.587
<i> Not as bad as the biopsy,</i>
<i> right?</i>

37:03.722 --> 37:05.522
- (chuckles humourlessly)

37:06.825 --> 37:08.658
<i> Can you feel that?</i>

37:08.694 --> 37:11.127
- No, don't feel a thing.
- Great.

37:12.998 --> 37:15.197
I'm going to insert a needle
between your vertebrae.

37:16.401 --> 37:17.467
- 'kay.

37:17.469 --> 37:19.402
- You're doing great.

37:19.537 --> 37:21.871
<i> Needle's in.</i>

37:22.007 --> 37:25.608
<i> Now I'm just trying to get</i>
<i> a little fluid.</i>

37:32.884 --> 37:35.084
(spinal fluid drips)

37:36.989 --> 37:38.288
- How's it going back there,
doc?

37:38.423 --> 37:40.423
- Great. You're doing great.

37:41.827 --> 37:44.060
(dripping quickly)

37:44.195 --> 37:47.030
- H-how long will it take
before the results come back?

37:47.032 --> 37:48.531
- Not long.

37:48.667 --> 37:51.367
- Mm. I just...

37:51.403 --> 37:53.602
Wanna know if I have cancer.

37:56.107 --> 37:57.373
- Grandpa!

37:57.409 --> 38:00.910
(birds chirp)

38:00.946 --> 38:02.378
Grandpa!

38:02.514 --> 38:04.447
(gasping for breath)

38:05.851 --> 38:08.384
(blows out his breath,
running footsteps)

38:09.855 --> 38:11.788
(car rumbles)

38:12.858 --> 38:14.390
(breathing hard)

38:15.527 --> 38:17.593
I've lost grandpa.
(door clicks open)

38:17.595 --> 38:19.996
- What? What do you mean,
you've lost grandpa?

38:20.131 --> 38:23.132
- We were birdwatching
and I just saw a hawk and...

38:23.168 --> 38:24.668
He's gone, okay?!

38:24.803 --> 38:26.736
- Great. Just show me
where you last were.

38:28.173 --> 38:30.473
- I circled, and I retraced,

38:30.542 --> 38:33.142
And I backtracked.

38:33.178 --> 38:36.212
Um... I think we should
get grandpa a tracker.

38:36.214 --> 38:37.947
- I just... I... I don't know
how much longer

38:38.016 --> 38:39.683
He's gonna be able to do things
on his own, ross.

38:39.818 --> 38:41.217
I just wanna--
- well, yeah, but I,

38:41.219 --> 38:42.418
I didn't mean like a leash,
mom.

38:42.454 --> 38:44.320
I just meant like an app.

38:45.991 --> 38:48.691
- Yeah. We can,
we can look into that.

38:48.727 --> 38:50.626
- (sighs heavily)

38:50.662 --> 38:52.362
- It's his jacket!

38:53.565 --> 38:55.831
(crow caws)

38:55.867 --> 38:57.967
(branches rustle)

38:59.170 --> 39:01.103
(yelling) dad?!

39:01.139 --> 39:02.705
<i> Gordon: Yeah, I'm over here!</i>

39:02.774 --> 39:04.340
- Yeah, dad, it's us!

39:04.376 --> 39:06.776
Just stay exactly where
you are, okay?

39:06.778 --> 39:08.344
<i> Gordon: I'm fine.</i>

39:08.347 --> 39:11.013
<i> Ross: (blows out his breath)</i>
<i> oh, I was worried.</i>

39:11.083 --> 39:13.115
- Hey, it's okay.

39:13.151 --> 39:15.919
He's okay. All right?
- (blows out his breath)

39:15.921 --> 39:17.453
Okay.

39:20.092 --> 39:22.124
- Ross, honey,

39:23.228 --> 39:24.928
I release you.

39:24.930 --> 39:26.663
- From what?

39:26.798 --> 39:29.732
- I release you from
the responsibility of grandpa.

39:29.735 --> 39:32.268
Okay? He's resilient, and you...

39:32.270 --> 39:34.003
You need to be 19.
- Mm.

39:34.139 --> 39:35.738
Come on.

39:35.741 --> 39:37.139
(yelling) don't move, dad!

39:37.175 --> 39:39.375
(crow caws, cicadas buzz)

39:42.914 --> 39:44.547
Do you see him?
- Yeah.

39:44.682 --> 39:46.349
Oh gee.

39:46.418 --> 39:47.750
What're you doing?

39:47.753 --> 39:49.819
- Oh, there's my coat!

39:49.821 --> 39:51.487
- Oh, there's my dad!

39:51.523 --> 39:53.556
- Where have you been?
- Sorry.

39:53.691 --> 39:55.558
Okay, maybe I got
a little lost, but...

39:55.594 --> 39:57.493
Look what I found?
Do you believe this?

39:57.529 --> 39:59.529
This is amazing!
Look at this!

39:59.664 --> 40:01.030
- Yeah.
- I may have,

40:01.166 --> 40:02.498
I may have wandered off
the trail,

40:02.634 --> 40:04.300
But I found this place.
Isn't it amazing?

40:04.436 --> 40:06.102
- This is really nice.
- It's beautiful.

40:06.237 --> 40:07.904
<i> - I mean, who knew</i>
<i> our new place</i>

40:07.973 --> 40:10.172
<i> Would be adjacent</i>
<i> to a spot like this?</i>

40:10.208 --> 40:12.107
- Yeah.
- This is sweet.

40:12.144 --> 40:13.576
- You'd find it.
- (chuckles)

40:13.711 --> 40:15.411
(water burbles)

40:15.447 --> 40:17.513
Oh yeah.

40:17.649 --> 40:20.115
Listen, stay right here,
take your time.

40:20.152 --> 40:21.651
We'll stick to the main path,
huh?

40:21.786 --> 40:24.120
- I'll try not to wander off.

40:24.255 --> 40:25.922
- Very funny.
- Yeah.

40:30.162 --> 40:32.294
(birds chirp, water burbles)

40:33.432 --> 40:38.568
♪♪♪

40:38.703 --> 40:41.403
(stones crunch underfoot)

40:43.141 --> 40:47.744
♪♪♪

40:47.879 --> 40:50.546
(water splashes lightly)

40:53.051 --> 40:55.952
(birds chirp, water burbles)

40:57.288 --> 40:58.420
(letter rustles)

40:58.457 --> 41:00.556
(grass crunches underfoot,
birds chirp, doves coo)

41:08.766 --> 41:10.266
- Hello.

41:10.268 --> 41:12.568
(letter crinkles)
- clark.

41:14.172 --> 41:16.105
(shoes thump)
what're you doing at my house?

41:17.375 --> 41:18.975
- I like your look.

41:19.044 --> 41:20.376
- What?

41:20.512 --> 41:22.512
Oh, um... It's not a look,

41:22.647 --> 41:24.914
It's an at-home... Look.

41:24.916 --> 41:26.582
Sorry, uh...

41:28.286 --> 41:30.185
Something wrong
with the inquest?

41:30.222 --> 41:31.921
- Yeah, kinda.

41:34.526 --> 41:37.126
- Are you gonna tell me?

41:37.262 --> 41:38.795
- I'm trying to decide
if you're the kind of person

41:38.930 --> 41:42.532
Who likes to know, or the kind
of person who doesn't.

41:42.534 --> 41:44.200
- Okay. Um...

41:44.335 --> 41:45.935
I don't appreciate you
coming to my house,

41:45.937 --> 41:49.405
So you can... Call me tomorrow
or email me.

41:49.541 --> 41:51.007
- I'm here as a professional
courtesy.

41:51.076 --> 41:53.609
We got an anonymous tip
about your sister's death.

41:55.080 --> 41:56.679
- Saying what?

41:56.814 --> 41:58.414
- It's about your dad.

42:00.385 --> 42:02.818
The way she fell
is suspicious.

42:02.854 --> 42:04.954
- Yeah, well, are you gonna
open a case against my dad

42:05.089 --> 42:07.289
Because of this?
- I'm not saying that, but...

42:07.325 --> 42:09.025
I have to look into it.

42:09.094 --> 42:11.427
- And who, uh,
who put in the tip?

42:11.463 --> 42:12.828
- You know I can't
disclose that.

42:12.864 --> 42:14.897
- Let me guess. It's an inmate
from a correctional facility

42:14.966 --> 42:16.566
Named kelly hart?

42:16.701 --> 42:19.168
I helped put her in jail,
and this door is closed.

42:19.304 --> 42:21.370
- I'm just the messenger.

42:21.406 --> 42:23.372
Oh, this means you have
to recuse yourself

42:23.441 --> 42:24.740
From our inquest.

42:24.776 --> 42:27.976
- Uh, no.
No, that's my inquest.

42:27.978 --> 42:30.913
- Rota fortuna, jenny.
Fortune's wheel.

42:30.949 --> 42:32.315
It was nice working with you.

42:32.317 --> 42:34.850
And note to self:
You like to know.

42:37.722 --> 42:39.521
(door clicks open)

42:41.125 --> 42:43.593
(door bangs shut,
engine starts)

42:45.797 --> 42:47.896
(jeep backs up)

42:50.769 --> 42:52.335
(jeep rumbles away)

42:54.272 --> 42:56.606
(opera music fades in
and out)

42:56.608 --> 42:57.941
(taps letter)

42:58.076 --> 43:05.214
♪♪♪

43:05.350 --> 43:06.815
- (muffled scream)

43:08.386 --> 43:09.685
Dammit!

43:11.056 --> 43:12.288
Ow!

43:12.423 --> 43:13.789
(footsteps crunch,
birds chirp)

43:15.460 --> 43:18.761
♪♪♪

43:18.830 --> 43:20.897
(operatic music plays)

43:21.032 --> 43:27.970
♪♪♪

43:28.006 --> 43:34.911
♪♪♪

43:35.046 --> 43:41.917
